      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>1-Chloro-1,2-diphenylethane can undergo E2 elimination to give either <i>cis</i>- or <i>trans</i>-1,2-diphenylethylene (stilbene). Draw Newman projections of the reactive conformations leading to both possible products, and suggest a reason why the <i>trans</i> alkene is the major product.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdDRUIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6e593a8c8f216f72989ae76c2701bcd741bb8711/OChem_11_EC_026.jpg\" alt=\"The conversion of 1-chloro-1,2-diphenylethane to trans-1,2-Diphenylethylene in the presence of methoxy ion.\">",
